-- BNP Got ‘Signs of Interest’ for Egypt Unit, Decraene Tells Echos
-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 2012-08-16T07:29:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/bnp-got-signs-of-interest-for-egypt-unit-decraene-tells-echos.html
BNP Paribas SA (BNP)  got “several signs
of interest” for its Egyptian consumer-banking unit,  Les Echos 
reported, citing Stefaan Decraene, the bank’s head of
international retail banking.  BNP Paribas may invite within 15 days potential bidders to
file preliminary offers for the Egyptian unit, the daily
newspaper also reported, without saying where it got the
information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fabio Benedetti-Valentini in Paris at 
